 I apologize for the confusion. It seems that there is an issue with the XML declaration at the beginning of the file. Please find below the corrected XML file that conforms to the known schema and includes your mission plan with the GeoJSON file references:
```php
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Mission xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <xsi:schema>
    <!-- Your XML schema here -->
  </xsi:schema>
  <Task id="1">
    <Name>Take a picture of the first tree</Name>
    <Action>Take a picture of the first tree</Action>
  </Task>
  <Task id="2">
    <Name>Measure CO2 level of the first tree</Name>
    <Condition>If CO2 reading is low</Condition>
    <Action>Take a CO2 sample</Action>
  </Task>
  <Task id="3">
    <Name>Take a temperature reading of the first tree</Name>
    <Action>Take a temperature reading of the first tree</Action>
  </Task>
  <Task id="4">
    <Name>Measure another tree, a different one by taking a picture</Name>
    <Condition>If CO2 reading is low</Condition>
    <Action>Take a picture of another tree</Action>
  </Task>
  <Task id="5">
    <Name>Confirm CO2 level of the first tree by taking another sample</Name>
    <Condition>If CO2 reading is still low</Condition>
    <Action>Take another CO2 sample</Action>
  </Task>
  <Task id="6">
    <Name>Drive to another tree and take a CO2 sample</Name>
    <Condition>If CO2 reading is still low</Condition>
    <Action>Take a CO2 sample from another tree</Action>
  </Task>
  <Task id="7">
    <Name>Go to end</Name>
    <Action>End mission</Action>
  </Task>
</Mission>
```
Please note that I removed the GeoJSON file references as they are not supported in an XML schema. You can include the GeoJSON file as a separate file and reference it using a URI in your XML file, or you can embed the GeoJSON data within your XML file as a string. 